reviews_data.review_text: We stumbled upon this boba tea shop during our shopping excursion at the Premium Outlet. The service was friendly and efficient. Our boba tea came out very quickly and it was very tasty. Our kids approved! Highly recommend!
Amazing doughnuts and coffee
best boba i’ve had in clt
Bangin place with banger people woking shoutouts to Sylinna for being a swag worker got me my tea quick 5/5 experiance

The cutest place to get your mochi doughnuts & boba! The staff is great if you have questions or suggestions. Love that the donuts rotate flavors, so you can get something new almost every time you go.

appreciate them remaking my mango drink as the one i ordered had tahine and spices in it. After one sip I almost jumped out of a moving car lmao. But anyway they were very nice in remaking a mango smoothie without any of the other stuff.
Very nice and cozy café! I went on a Thursday afternoon and it was such an amazing experience. The mochi donuts taste so good!!!

Was pretty good. Mochi donuts were possibly the best in Charlotte - Andes mint chocolate and strawberry were quite nice. Beverages were pretty good, too.

Hard to hear the cashier with the "COVID condom" still in place, but it is it what it is.

Spendy, but, would return.

Such a cute place with great atmosphere and friendly staff. The churro mochi donut and taro milk tea were delicious, not too sweet at all! My kiddo loved the mango tea with mango boba and the strawberry sprinkle donut.

Service was excellent and loved the menu options. I will definitely be coming back again soon. The shop is very nice and vibrant along with the treats being both reasonable in price and mind blowing in quality! I like the boba they have but their mochi donuts are even better! Definitely give them a try when you visit. You won't regret it.

Love these guys!!! Everything’s always good, aesthetics are peak, and everyone’s super nice. I’ve travelled a lot and Moji is definitely one of my favorite boba places I’ve been to in the country! I come here a bit too frequently lol
If you like brown sugar milk tea, they have a really good one hear. Really neat vibe and aesthetic as well.
Our favorite boba place in charlotte
I really love their mochi donuts and how unique and tasty it is.  In addition they also change their limited flavors every week if I'm not mistaken adding more variety to their menu
We enjoyed it!!!
Cuteeee place !!!
Amazing service! The mochi donuts and drinks were delicious!!
The donuts are always amazing!
Love it here!! Always consistent with their drinks and also great customer service!! 😁
First time and I'm from SD.  This is pretty good boba.  You can really taste the Macha powder which I like.

This is the best milk tea place in the area! Their signature milk tea is great, they have the best boba, and the mochi donuts are delicious. I love that they rotate the donut flavors so there's always a new one I can try. Lavender milk tea is my favorite though, I check every week hoping it comes back
Had the ginger milk tea with boba; milk tea was good, ginger was very subtle (wish it was stronger). Tapioca pearls were not bad. Nice decor
Stopped in this morning for a mochi donut and boba and the service was excellent! The vanilla chai mochi donut was excellent and the guava energy tea was great with the recommended mango boba! Yum.

Best bubble tea in CLT to date! Go to is the Mango Green Tea with coconut jelly and boba. Seat swing is a nice touch to
the vibe and the donuts are a great treat!

The tea drinks are either super watered down or taste chemically and gross. Me and my partner have gone here plenty of times because theres no other option for bobas in our area but this last time i ordered a matcha milk tea and a donut set it in stone for me. The milk tea was flavorless, it tasted like water and they barely added any boba which was also flavorless. Theres no reason to pay $8 for  for colored water rather than go to sharetea thats 11 miles away which is well worth it. Theres a new one in the area that will come soon.
Super cute place! We love Moji for boba and donuts!! They are friendly, prompt, and offer a discount if you pay cash! 💲

This place is awesome!
When you enter it’s like you’re going into an entirely different world- excellent decorations and atmosphere!

They have a lot of options- I love that you can adjust the sweetness and ice levels to your desires. Their specialty milk tea was superb!
I’ll definitely be back with the whole family to try some more things- try it out, you’ll have a great experience too!
First time visiting this spot today and it did not disappoint. We sampled each of the mochi donuts and they were delicious along with the moji Boba latte 🧋🍩. ❤️❤️
Love this place! Very clean and friendly staff. The tea was super refreshing! The macarons and donuts were delicious as well.
I love this place. The teas and coffees are delicious, and it’s one of the most relaxing environments that I’ve been too. It’s a great atmosphere with a beautiful interior. I cannot recommend enough.

Their Thai tea is not great. My husband had the coconut smoothie and he enjoyed it, but when we asked for the amount leftover in the blender, they said they didn't do that. They'd rather dump it down the drain than give it to their paying costumer.
Best Boba spot in the Charlotte area.

I was immediately greeted with a smile from the young female cashier. She was kind enough to patiently wait for me to navigate the menu all the while answering any questions I had. After placing a fairly large order, I was given a pager to notify me when the pastries were ready as they were made to order.  The Oolong boboa tea was delicious.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Mochi Donuts, Coconut Waffle, Mochi Doughnuts, Macarons, Frusty Mochi Donut, Coffee Jelly

reviews_data.review_text: Get a churro donut!
Cute little place I love to stop by for boba and mochi donuts whenever I’m in the area. They never disappoint and the decorum is very cute and chill.

I couldn’t say more wonderful things about this tea house. The atmosphere is beautiful, there is a swing, a gorgeous mural on the wall, and calm music that they have playing.
The drinks are customizable to EXACTLY what you’d like, even down to how much sugar and ice. I was able to get my favorite kind of tea, and it was incredible.
We had macarons as well, while they had been busy prior and sold out of several things, there were still many options- and the macarons were to DIE for.
It’s not a restaurant, but the sweet treats and seating area definitely makes for a cozy place to have a snack.
Can’t wait to return!
Cute shop and yummy donuts!

Been coming here once a week for the past month and I dont see that changing anytime soon. The donuts are fantastic and mochi donuts are a little less sugary than your typical donut. I’ve yet to have a tea flavor I haven’t enjoyed, but the strawberry yogurt and taro have been my favorite. This place rocks

Wow!!! It's definitely a must if you wanted to try any type of boba tea blended.  First, I came in with lots of questions cause everything I was eye tasting, lol. The guy taking our order was very friendly and patient with me while I was ordering for a hit minute.  The decor of the places made it very adventurous to be here. We enjoyed our drinks so much we ordered another set to go.  The mochi donut was chewy with a funnel cake taste. Yummy! I can see me taking the long trip to try this place again

This place is just okay in my opinion. Very beautiful, instagramable place but lacking in the sweets department. I did not know the moji donuts are premade with their premade flavors. We went during the afternoon and were told they only had 3 flavors left to choose from. We chose the Oreo matcha which had a great flavor and the lavender lemon which was just okay. The donuts were not warmed up which I’m not used to; they were room temperature which didn’t make them as appetizing. The place we normally go allows us to choose any moji donut flavor because it’s made to order. They come warm and melt in your mouth - these did not. My boba milk tea was good but there’s so many other boba places that I wouldn’t come out my way to have boba here again.
Cool staff and lots of options for teas, desserts and mochi donuts.
Great date places to stop by
My first time in a tea shop. The lady behind the counter was very helpful helping me choose. The tea was very good and I'll be back.

Cheese foam is to die for!

I would recommend trying it with their strawberry drink for great mouth feels! TO add on, try the coconut waffle and dip it inside the drink!

NO WI-FI. Came here to study with my fiancé as we both have big professional exams upcoming. The tea was great and employees were nice. BUT I am not sure how a coffee or tea shop would not have WI-FI. VERY DISAPPOINTING.
Beautiful place. Was craving Boba, brown sugar, 100% sweetness and mochi donuts! Perfect spot and absolutely delicious.

It's a good place for a to-go order, no more chance for dining. They don't have a plate and knife.

At least they have Napkin and spoon in there.
Great first experience here!! Heard some good things and had to stop by after lunch for bubble tea and donuts. Everything was so delicious!
Very nice place! I don’t like tea, but theirs was good!
Taro boba drink is good
The donuts were so yummy!

My oldest son came home with less than half of his cup oh tea🥤😅 we asked him what was he drinking because the cup looked nice 👍 my wife and i tried it and 😱 and i drove immediately to get a milk taro tea 🥤and the churro donuts 🍩 🤤🤤🤤🤤🤤 that's a great combination if you ask me 👍 i totally recommend this place 😀

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Frusty Mochi Donut, Taro Milk Smoothie

reviews_data.review_text: This place is so cute and the staff is super friendly! Huge variety of teas and toppings. Their mochi donuts are the best! Their flavors do change weekly so check their Facebook or instagram for what they have. The Biscoff is my favorite!

This is a super cool boba shop that also sells tasty desserts like macarons, mochi donuts, and waffles. I love the atmosphere and the decor, it’s so relaxing. This place has a few booths and a couple of tables for seating, and I also really enjoy the swing bench.
super fresh and yummy! never had macaroons and they had a variety of flavors I couldn’t help myself.

Love the atmosphere! The esthetic id beautiful and the boba tea was delicious! I ordered an ube matcha latte, my husband a passion fruit and a few mochi donuts. I took a star off because although everything was soo good, some donuts where a bit too sweet for my liking. Definitely a must try though!

The black sugar milk tea was so good, one of the best boba drinks I’ve had in Charlotte. It tastes exactly like the “classic” milk tea flavor in Asia I that grew up with.
On the other hand the roasted oolong tea was bland and had a strange aftertaste.
The donuts were pretty good and chewy. The drinks did take longer than usual, we waited maybe 30 minutes for four drinks
Overall a great experience.

Nice and clean establishment. Stopped by around 3pm on a Friday and it wasn't too busy.

Ordered a total of 5 drinks and they pushed out the drinks fairly quick. Service was great as well.

I'd recommend this place to any boba lover.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Lychee Slush, Strawberry Green, Passion Fruit Juice, Coconut Jelly, Strawberry Milk, Honeydew Green

reviews_data.review_text: Good experience, great service

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Mochi Doughnuts, Coconut Milk Smoothie, Coffee Jelly

reviews_data.review_text: I placed a large order for my wedding and the donuts were a hit. All my guests loved the oreo, matcha, and strawberry flavored mochi donuts. I highly recommend Moji Teahouse for yummy mochi donuts.
Super nice place and their mango juice tastes great, love their popping boba and snack variety
Made a trip over to the area and was not disappointed! Service was quick and easy. No wait which was great. Happy with our order, tasted great. Nice atmosphere for photos too.
I tried this first time especially for donuts but i m so disappointed because donuts are cold it taste not good to me n drinks are ok
Love the interior and tasty food.

I don't know how good this place is.  My daughter bought a few tasty little snacks and a tee. I only know that she threw the tee away and didn't drink it. Also, she has not asked to go back. We have been by there many times since. Never had she asked to go back, not even once.
never tried asian donuts before. Love it! coming back for sure
Delicious honeydew milk tea. Very nice and helpful staff.
Love the atmosphere, really nice employees and awesome drinks 🧋:)

Amazing atmosphere and team members who want to help create a great community of Tea enjoyers!!

Thank You and I will be back to try more soon!!
Came for the moji donuts and was not disappointed 😋 it was good! The tea was is good too but interior design was so cute with felt livey. Nice employees as well
Their mochi donut was delicious. Their Boba tea was ok. The atmosphere is beautiful

I live in Asia so it's hard to impress me when it comes to Boba tea. However I was very impressed by this place and the drinks were delicious and the prices are reasonable. My only suggestion to the owner is to add more tapiokas to the large drinks because I ran out of them before I was finished with my drink. Usually in Asia you have plenty of tapiokas left after the drink part is done. But overall I'm satisfied and I'll be back!
Just meh
Tea is okay. Not the best. Raspberry donut is great.

I was craving bubble tea and man I was so disappointed in the tapioca balls. Some were  chewy and some were still hard, it could literally be a choking hazard. Please make sure your tapioca balls are cooked all the way. The drink would have been so perfect but I literally had to keep spitting out every other ball because it wasn't chewable. Donuts we're great though.
Love it..such a cute place with delicious coffee and donuts!
Probably best place to get bubble tea in Charlotte. We tried many and this place beats on all categories: flavor, design, cleanliness, choices etc.

This place is AMAZING! If you’ve been to Japan then you know this is just like Mister Donuts. I’ve been craving for their donuts and OMG! Now I don’t have to fly to Japan to get their donuts. This is the PLACE! Amazing customer service! ♥️
Love the bubble tea here, I always get the taro. The mango pearls are delicious and appreciate the ability to customize sugar and ice levels.
Boba was hard and took over 25 minutes to get my one drink
Great service, friendly staff, and delicious Mochi Donuts!
Nice and quite place to enjoy your drink. I love it. Thanks for a great service.
Delicious 🫠🫠🫠
Gotta try their little donuts, and the boba and coffee are always on point!

Tasty mochi donuts and a refreshing variety of teas and juices, only slightly pricey. Too bad its popularity made for a 40-minute standing wait to order and 30-minute standing wait to enjoy a to-go order. A very popular spot for hanging out on a Sunday afternoon for area young people further narrows limited seating for customers. Donut varieties number only six per week, though flavors are  changed often.
amazing place! great employees, wonderful service too. definitely recommend

Everything I had was so yummy!
Was eyeing out this place for a while and decided to give it a try. Had a Condensed  Milk Latte and it delivered the right coffee flavor and sweetness, my boyfriend had a coconut milk tea boba and it the flavor was really refreshing.
The mochi donuts became my new favorite treat, we had their valentine’s special flavors and all were great, especially the strawberry cheesecake (i think that’s what it was) and the sakura one, all of them fresh, fluffy and not overly sweet.

Definitely recommend this place!

super popular now so be prepared to wait in a line but the venue is BEAUTIFUL and the staff is incredible. well worth the wait. however I am sad they took spam musubi off of the menu and hope that item returns. they also have specials and decorations for holidays!

Try one of their yakult/yogurt drinks! My favorite is the strawberry. It's such a creamy and refreshing drink! Perfect if you're not a fan of milk tea. The staff is always super helpful and welcoming.
hella good
Great service and even greater drinks! The Coconut Milk Smoothie is to die for! 💯💯
Very lovely teahouse, there boba tea is one of the best i ever had would recommande.
This place is fire. Good food, (especially them donuts) and chill environment. I will definitely try to visit more often.
Best Tea place i’ve been to in a long time! Highly highly recommend.
Excellent customer service, seriously, they need more support!
Honestly amazing best staff ever
I love their Moji Boba Latte, their tapioca pearls are the best I’ve had in Charlotte.
Very bad customer service, change your mind if you planning to support this shop.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi there thank you for taking your time to letting us know your experience. I’m sorry if it wasn’t a pleasant one and would like to understand what happened during your visit. Please contact us so we can rectify any issues.

reviews_data.review_text: Very bad customer service 😡😡😡😡This shop opened for bully peoples🚫🚫DO NOT SUPPORT THEM🚫🚫I wish this shop will out of business as soon as possible😡😡😡
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi there. We’re a small family owned  business that would be affected by misunderstandings. I’m sorry there was a misunderstanding which we tried to explain what happened and willing to even show you video of the conversation during your visit but you left abruptly. We truly are welcoming of anyone and would like to offer you to contact us to sort the misunderstanding out. Thank you again for your time.

reviews_data.review_text: Awesome spot, best milk tea in the area
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi John, thank you for taking your time to leaving us a feedback. We appreciate you and hope to see you again.

reviews_data.review_text: Mmm pandan waffle...
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your time on leaving us your feedback. That’s definitely a popular item here. See you again!

reviews_data.review_text: Last minute stop for mochi donuts, definitely worth it!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for taking your time to leaving us a review! We love our mochi donuts and flavors change every week. Hope to see you soon!

reviews_data.review_text: The brown sugar coffee latte is my favorite. This was my first time trying mochi donuts…I will not be going back to cake donuts. I’m excited to go back and try the macaroons on my next visit, they looked delicious.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Stacey! Thank you for taking your time to leaving us a review! We appreciate your business and hope to see you soon!

reviews_data.review_text: I got a coconut bubble tea and it was delicious, you can request your level of sugar so it’s not too sweet. First time trying mochi donuts and it was so yummy!! Will be back again!
Very friendly folks
Favorite tea place, always excited to come here.
Wide menu, very tasty, great service.

Beautiful tea bar where you can enjoy a cozy atmosphere, boba tea, mochi donuts, and much more. Things are priced fairly and I'm glad this place opened up so close to the outlets! They have a variety of boba pearls including mango and brown sugar which we love.
Friendly staff + very calm atmosphere

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Mochi Doughnuts, Matcha Milk Smoothie, Honeydew Green

reviews_data.review_text:
I ordered Roasted Oolong Milk Tea with Boba. And 1/2 dozen of Mochi donuts( Strawberry Matcha, Frusty, Christmas something..etc). And Panda Coconut Waffle. I am so glad to visit here. It's far from my home. But it was definitely worth it.  And I can choose Oatmilk for Oolong Milk tea!! The taste is sooo amazing . I recommend Strawberry Matcha, Rudolph Mochi Donut. Also, the interior was so cute :) I will definitely visit again  :)

(The only thing that would've made it even better was if the Mochi Donut had been warm;))

Such a cute shop and the customer service was fantastic! The gentleman who helped us helped me pick out what I wanted without acting annoyed or frustrated I was needing help (pregnant and needed boba thats caffeine free and wasn't sure on my options). Super fast in preparation and everything was SO GOOD. Will absolutely be going back.
This place was adorable ! We enjoyed a Boba tea and a variety of mochi donuts that were fantastic! The customer service was great. We can’t wait to return .
Dulce de Leche, Fruity Pebbles, and Strawberry Dragoonfruit!!!!!! So good!!!!!
Good boba, some drinks are diff like thai tea but oolong & jasmine milk tea r good
Very delicious! The mochi donuts (especially the matcha) were amazing! Definitely want to go back for other goodies!
10/10 recommend! My favorite drink is the taro milk tea with boba. The musubi and donuts are yummy as well.
Amazing boba tea and delicious donuts too!
Got the taro smoothie and it was ok. Ice wasn’t blended too well and some boba was very soft and some was slightly hard. Consistency was off but nice decors and clean building.
I love the mochi donuts and the milk tea!
This is my favorite place for boba tea! The cheese foam is so delicious 😋
Very good boba tea and donuts
moji doughnuts are unique and taste so good! Milk tea with bona are also good!

I am a repeat customer, and usually enjoy the tea. The young ladies at the register  are usually super nice, and patient. But today, my visit was not too satisfying, which is disappointing. I really like their tea, but sadly I will not be returning.
My complaint is:
I  arrived and  placed my drink order first,  prior to a caucasian gentleman,.
The  barista purposely made his drink before mine. I  politely asked why did the man get his  drink before me, and  the response was his drink was easier to make. That just did not sit right with me.
Orders should be made on a first come first  serve basis, and not which customer's drink is easier to make.
Being an African American woman,  or a person of color,  it made me feel uncomfortable , This type of   action towards a customer can be viewed  as discrimination, This incident may not have been intentional, but ,African Americans, or people of color do not always get the same customer service as  a non person of color. This is something that the  employee(s) of Moji Teahouse need to be mindful of. I see a lot of persons of color supporting the business,.
The employees may need some sensitivity training, or teaching tolerance lessons.. Sadly, I won't be returning because I enjoy the tea. I will take my business elsewhere.  Queen City Tea prepares their drinks on a first come first serve basis.
Fresh food, delicious drinks, and full of variety. the place is very cozy

Super yummy doughnuts! Their milk teas are really delicious too~
The decor is clean and chic, and even their hot cups are soooo pretty
So glad this is now a family owned business! Still offering great bubble tea, and now they offer delicious mochi doughnuts and other snacks.
Nice but need to wait sometime quite long time
Yummy assorted mochi donuts...banana, raspberry, cotton candy, chocolate pretzel, horchata, and coconut. Brown Sugar Milk Tea with Boba and Thai Tea with bobas.
So delicious! They have a huge selection of flavors and toppings. It’s super fresh and they’re always quick with service!
Loved their mochi donuts!
Love these Mochi donuts, and the drinks are amazing.  We went twice in 2 days and neither day disappointed!  Love the weekly change of flavors.
Love this place. Everything is delicious. Sometimes there is a wait but it’s so worth it. I recommend the Pandan waffle is so delicious!!

Very cute Boba tea shop! Every Monday will be busy due to daily weeks of different donuts flavors. They hand out buzzers for orders to be ready. They have golden boba/tapioca which other places does not. Which is similar to black/regular tapioca. Location used to be Ding Tea.

I found this place through Instagram and decided to try it out. It's a cute tiny place but it sure is quite popular. They have some adorable merchandise that looked for sale. They also had a small bench swing for photo opportunities. The selection was pretty big, and allowing for sugar and/or ice amount changes. I mainly came here for the mochi donuts. I had a pandan coconut Waffle, mochi donut and milk tea. It was reminiscent of shops you would find on the west coast. Even with 25% sugar, I found the tea to be a little too sweet. The Waffle was spongy and slightly sweet and just right for me. The donut had the chewy texture which I expected but just like the tea, it was a tad too sweet for my liking. Very cute aesthetic and good pricing.

Came the first time when they rebranded asked for 4 different things on the menu literally out of everything decided to just leave. Came back on a Tuesday,waited about 40 minutes for 2mochi donuts,not worth the money.stale donuts.

Found this place on instagram. We went on a Sunday and the line was very long. We waited about 25 mins to order. I ordered a mochi donut which was kind of expensive ($3.50) a large tarp smoothie and 2 spam musbi which were delicious. The place is beautiful inside as well
fire donuts
The team here is awesome. Order is always on point. Come see them.
the moji boba latte is the milk base and brown sugar boba, it’s so good! i finished and honestly wish i got a bigger one!

Been a regular since before they rebranded. I went 3 times this past week, and my last visit was the day after the Instagram post. Of course, due to the post the line was long and so was the wait time. But the staff was as friendly as usual and they were working diligently to get the orders out as best they could under the circumstances. Their boba tea is delicious and so are their Mochi Donuts. If you’re visiting for the first time since the Instagram post, be patient because, of course wait times will be longer than usual. But their friendliness and positive attitude certainly compensates the wait. Enjoy the Moji Teahouse experience as well as the cute aesthetic look, everyone! 🙂

I saw good reviews on this location. I arrived around 11:48am ish and things went smoothly. Each donut is $3.50 each (plus tax). That's a bit expensive for me. I believe a dozen costs $30. I bought a milk tea and 1 donut. The donut was good, but I don't think it was worth $3.50. After I order, more people started to arrive. The line ended outside (the entrance of the store.) It was getting very crowded and I decided to leave. If you plan on coming here, get there early.
As for the Milk tea, it's average. I would rather go to gong Cha.

Waited 30 minutes to order 3 mochi doughnuts. Then another 40 minutes just to get them despite plenty of doughnuts waiting on the shelves as the staff were busy making bubble tea orders. You'd think orders with ready made items could've been fulfilled before others just to get customers out the door. Staff were slow and unorganised with no sense of urgency despite the queue out the door.

Doughnuts were decent at least.

Came here on a Friday afternoon. We expected not to be crowded but there was a line. We waited 30 mins to get to the front of the line. People were waiting to get their boba drinks for seemingly a long time. We decided to skip beverages since it seemed like the wait for boba was taking too long. We just ordered 3 mochi donuts so we didn’t have to wait another 30+ mins. Don’t come here if you have somewhere to be! Hoping that when Mochinuts opens soon, the ordering process will be smoother and faster. Drove down here from Concord. Will not return.

My husband and I tried Ding Tea, but just recently came back for the first time since they rebranded and changed up their menu a bit.

We shared:
- Pandan Coconut Waffle
- Lychee Strawberry and Passion Fruit Mochi Donuts
- Passion Fruit Macaron

The mochi donuts were great. I loved both flavors. They change their flavors every Monday. The Pandan waffle was also very good.

I'm happy to have a place like this in Steele Creek. We don't usually get cool places in the area. I'll be back for more mochi donuts.
Mochi Donuts are good, but they're $3.50 each and $30 for a dozen.  Come on now, that's super overpriced.  My wife and I got 4 mochi donut, 2 drinks and it was $28. Lol
Best boba tea in town and dont get me started on their mochi donuts … MOUTH WATERING!
Awesome boba tea shop. Love the varieties of drinks  and mochi donuts. Atmosphere is very welcoming and the people are really nice. Definitely recommend!

I was visiting family in NC and heard this teahouse had Dole soft serve, but they were sold out when I arrived, so boba was on the menu. I’ve been drinking boba since 2000 when it was introduced to Hawaii from Japan and I gotta tell you I was surprised. Beyond the kind and friendly staff the drinks took me back to when I first had boba as a kid. We had a big size group so we had a little of everything and they all were amazing to great. I will definitely be back next time I’m in town.
The tea here is great and the staff are so nice!
I come here so much everyone knows my name 🤣. I never thought it could get any better but then they added mochi donuts & new drinks
My favorite bubble tea in town! So yummy! And the bubbles are always perfectly soft with a touch of sweetness… a hit & miss @ most other places I visited.

10/10 service and food
Great atmosphere and we love the new pager system!
My partner and I come here every weekend to get our boba fix 💖🧋💖
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Drake for leaving us a review. We appreciate all the support. Hope yo see you again soon.

reviews_data.review_text: I went there with my boyfriend on the weekend and the staff was so friendly and helpful even though they were busy! Giving me constant updates when my donuts would be ready was very attentive by them. Constant changes of flavors is so unique  and all of them were so tasty! Highly recommend if you’re in the area!
The cuties TeaHouse here in Charlotte and best house milk tea I ever had. The staff are super pleasant which makes the overall experience enjoyable.
Love the customizable tea and mochi donuts! U can taste your drinks before it's sealed and they will adjust anything u ask for. Just ask. Great staff!

I am absolutely in LOVE with this place. The fact that their flavors of mochi donuts change out EVERY WEEK? and they're super innovative flavors! Never even heard of 80% of these flavors but I am always excited to try all of them! The boba and drinks are also amazing! The staff and customer service is also wonderful! Whatever you guys are doing, keep doing it! Always a great experience every time I come :)
LOVE this place! Will go back each time. Tapioca pearls are perfect and they make it just like I ask.
Great drinks and great people!
the shop is so cute and I love the boba drinks and donuts from there! I definitely  recommend going there with your friends and family!
One of the best boba places nearby I love to go to as well as my friends and family!!!
The best boba in town! Not to mention their mochi donuts are so delicious. Can’t wait to come back! Friendly staff as well!
Loved the atmosphere, super cute and friendly. Not to mention the food and boba drinks were amazing. I can’t wait to go back
My friend told me about this place and Omg its the best Tapioca spot in Charlotte!! They got some really yummy food items too!! Glad I stopped by.
i love this place. i’ve been coming here for years and there upgrade is better , the drinks here are my favorite
staff were very nice to every customer inside, helped my cousin get the order he wanted
I ordered signature milk tea and it tastes like milk mixed with sweet tea.

reviews_data.review_text:
Drinks were lack-luster. No flavor at all. Called the store back to ask for a refund and the manager on duty tried to give an excuse instead of an explanation. She was very passive aggressive and condescending during our whole conversation but did return our money. Store was clean.

3 out of 5 drinks were adjusted to light ice. Most boba places add more tea, creamer, syrup and sugar to accommodate for the ice adjustment. Seems like they only added tea to fill the rest of the cup and called it a day.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Julie, thanks for coming by our store. Your drinks were adjusted to slight ice so to accommodate any ice adjustments more tea is added. We welcome all customers to sample their drinks before sealing to make sure they’re satisfied. We offered to make your drinks again to your taste in which you declined. Majority of the drinks here are customizable so sugar levels and tea levels change. Just ask us for a sample before sealing it and we would be glad to make it to your taste.

reviews_data.review_text: Of course the teas are flavorful and so good now you can pair it with mochi donuts!!The mochi donuts are so delicious and has such perfect chewy texture! The hardest part is choosing my favorite flavor!

reviews_data.review_text: We stumbled upon this boba tea shop during our shopping excursion at the Premium Outlet. The service was friendly and efficient. Our boba tea came out very quickly and it was very tasty. Our kids approved! Highly recommend!
Amazing doughnuts and coffee
best boba i’ve had in clt
Bangin place with banger people woking shoutouts to Sylinna for being a swag worker got me my tea quick 5/5 experiance

The cutest place to get your mochi doughnuts & boba! The staff is great if you have questions or suggestions. Love that the donuts rotate flavors, so you can get something new almost every time you go.

appreciate them remaking my mango drink as the one i ordered had tahine and spices in it. After one sip I almost jumped out of a moving car lmao. But anyway they were very nice in remaking a mango smoothie without any of the other stuff.
Very nice and cozy café! I went on a Thursday afternoon and it was such an amazing experience. The mochi donuts taste so good!!!

Was pretty good. Mochi donuts were possibly the best in Charlotte - Andes mint chocolate and strawberry were quite nice. Beverages were pretty good, too.

Hard to hear the cashier with the "COVID condom" still in place, but it is it what it is.

Spendy, but, would return.

Such a cute place with great atmosphere and friendly staff. The churro mochi donut and taro milk tea were delicious, not too sweet at all! My kiddo loved the mango tea with mango boba and the strawberry sprinkle donut.

Service was excellent and loved the menu options. I will definitely be coming back again soon. The shop is very nice and vibrant along with the treats being both reasonable in price and mind blowing in quality! I like the boba they have but their mochi donuts are even better! Definitely give them a try when you visit. You won't regret it.

Love these guys!!! Everything’s always good, aesthetics are peak, and everyone’s super nice. I’ve travelled a lot and Moji is definitely one of my favorite boba places I’ve been to in the country! I come here a bit too frequently lol
If you like brown sugar milk tea, they have a really good one hear. Really neat vibe and aesthetic as well.
Our favorite boba place in charlotte
I really love their mochi donuts and how unique and tasty it is.  In addition they also change their limited flavors every week if I'm not mistaken adding more variety to their menu
We enjoyed it!!!
Cuteeee place !!!
Amazing service! The mochi donuts and drinks were delicious!!
The donuts are always amazing!
Love it here!! Always consistent with their drinks and also great customer service!! 😁
First time and I'm from SD.  This is pretty good boba.  You can really taste the Macha powder which I like.

This is the best milk tea place in the area! Their signature milk tea is great, they have the best boba, and the mochi donuts are delicious. I love that they rotate the donut flavors so there's always a new one I can try. Lavender milk tea is my favorite though, I check every week hoping it comes back
Had the ginger milk tea with boba; milk tea was good, ginger was very subtle (wish it was stronger). Tapioca pearls were not bad. Nice decor
Stopped in this morning for a mochi donut and boba and the service was excellent! The vanilla chai mochi donut was excellent and the guava energy tea was great with the recommended mango boba! Yum.

Best bubble tea in CLT to date! Go to is the Mango Green Tea with coconut jelly and boba. Seat swing is a nice touch to
the vibe and the donuts are a great treat!

The tea drinks are either super watered down or taste chemically and gross. Me and my partner have gone here plenty of times because theres no other option for bobas in our area but this last time i ordered a matcha milk tea and a donut set it in stone for me. The milk tea was flavorless, it tasted like water and they barely added any boba which was also flavorless. Theres no reason to pay $8 for  for colored water rather than go to sharetea thats 11 miles away which is well worth it. Theres a new one in the area that will come soon.
Super cute place! We love Moji for boba and donuts!! They are friendly, prompt, and offer a discount if you pay cash! 💲

This place is awesome!
When you enter it’s like you’re going into an entirely different world- excellent decorations and atmosphere!

They have a lot of options- I love that you can adjust the sweetness and ice levels to your desires. Their specialty milk tea was superb!
I’ll definitely be back with the whole family to try some more things- try it out, you’ll have a great experience too!
First time visiting this spot today and it did not disappoint. We sampled each of the mochi donuts and they were delicious along with the moji Boba latte 🧋🍩. ❤️❤️
Love this place! Very clean and friendly staff. The tea was super refreshing! The macarons and donuts were delicious as well.
I love this place. The teas and coffees are delicious, and it’s one of the most relaxing environments that I’ve been too. It’s a great atmosphere with a beautiful interior. I cannot recommend enough.

Their Thai tea is not great. My husband had the coconut smoothie and he enjoyed it, but when we asked for the amount leftover in the blender, they said they didn't do that. They'd rather dump it down the drain than give it to their paying costumer.
Best Boba spot in the Charlotte area.

I was immediately greeted with a smile from the young female cashier. She was kind enough to patiently wait for me to navigate the menu all the while answering any questions I had. After placing a fairly large order, I was given a pager to notify me when the pastries were ready as they were made to order.  The Oolong boboa tea was delicious.

reviews_data.review_text: Get a churro donut!
Cute little place I love to stop by for boba and mochi donuts whenever I’m in the area. They never disappoint and the decorum is very cute and chill.

I couldn’t say more wonderful things about this tea house. The atmosphere is beautiful, there is a swing, a gorgeous mural on the wall, and calm music that they have playing.
The drinks are customizable to EXACTLY what you’d like, even down to how much sugar and ice. I was able to get my favorite kind of tea, and it was incredible.
We had macarons as well, while they had been busy prior and sold out of several things, there were still many options- and the macarons were to DIE for.
It’s not a restaurant, but the sweet treats and seating area definitely makes for a cozy place to have a snack.
Can’t wait to return!
Cute shop and yummy donuts!

Been coming here once a week for the past month and I dont see that changing anytime soon. The donuts are fantastic and mochi donuts are a little less sugary than your typical donut. I’ve yet to have a tea flavor I haven’t enjoyed, but the strawberry yogurt and taro have been my favorite. This place rocks

Wow!!! It's definitely a must if you wanted to try any type of boba tea blended.  First, I came in with lots of questions cause everything I was eye tasting, lol. The guy taking our order was very friendly and patient with me while I was ordering for a hit minute.  The decor of the places made it very adventurous to be here. We enjoyed our drinks so much we ordered another set to go.  The mochi donut was chewy with a funnel cake taste. Yummy! I can see me taking the long trip to try this place again

This place is just okay in my opinion. Very beautiful, instagramable place but lacking in the sweets department. I did not know the moji donuts are premade with their premade flavors. We went during the afternoon and were told they only had 3 flavors left to choose from. We chose the Oreo matcha which had a great flavor and the lavender lemon which was just okay. The donuts were not warmed up which I’m not used to; they were room temperature which didn’t make them as appetizing. The place we normally go allows us to choose any moji donut flavor because it’s made to order. They come warm and melt in your mouth - these did not. My boba milk tea was good but there’s so many other boba places that I wouldn’t come out my way to have boba here again.
Cool staff and lots of options for teas, desserts and mochi donuts.
Great date places to stop by
My first time in a tea shop. The lady behind the counter was very helpful helping me choose. The tea was very good and I'll be back.

Cheese foam is to die for!

I would recommend trying it with their strawberry drink for great mouth feels! TO add on, try the coconut waffle and dip it inside the drink!

NO WI-FI. Came here to study with my fiancé as we both have big professional exams upcoming. The tea was great and employees were nice. BUT I am not sure how a coffee or tea shop would not have WI-FI. VERY DISAPPOINTING.
Beautiful place. Was craving Boba, brown sugar, 100% sweetness and mochi donuts! Perfect spot and absolutely delicious.

It's a good place for a to-go order, no more chance for dining. They don't have a plate and knife.

At least they have Napkin and spoon in there.
Great first experience here!! Heard some good things and had to stop by after lunch for bubble tea and donuts. Everything was so delicious!
Very nice place! I don’t like tea, but theirs was good!
Taro boba drink is good
The donuts were so yummy!

My oldest son came home with less than half of his cup oh tea🥤😅 we asked him what was he drinking because the cup looked nice 👍 my wife and i tried it and 😱 and i drove immediately to get a milk taro tea 🥤and the churro donuts 🍩 🤤🤤🤤🤤🤤 that's a great combination if you ask me 👍 i totally recommend this place 😀

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Frusty Mochi Donut, Taro Milk Smoothie

reviews_data.review_text: This place is so cute and the staff is super friendly! Huge variety of teas and toppings. Their mochi donuts are the best! Their flavors do change weekly so check their Facebook or instagram for what they have. The Biscoff is my favorite!

This is a super cool boba shop that also sells tasty desserts like macarons, mochi donuts, and waffles. I love the atmosphere and the decor, it’s so relaxing. This place has a few booths and a couple of tables for seating, and I also really enjoy the swing bench.
super fresh and yummy! never had macaroons and they had a variety of flavors I couldn’t help myself.

Love the atmosphere! The esthetic id beautiful and the boba tea was delicious! I ordered an ube matcha latte, my husband a passion fruit and a few mochi donuts. I took a star off because although everything was soo good, some donuts where a bit too sweet for my liking. Definitely a must try though!

The black sugar milk tea was so good, one of the best boba drinks I’ve had in Charlotte. It tastes exactly like the “classic” milk tea flavor in Asia I that grew up with.
On the other hand the roasted oolong tea was bland and had a strange aftertaste.
The donuts were pretty good and chewy. The drinks did take longer than usual, we waited maybe 30 minutes for four drinks
Overall a great experience.

Nice and clean establishment. Stopped by around 3pm on a Friday and it wasn't too busy.

Ordered a total of 5 drinks and they pushed out the drinks fairly quick. Service was great as well.

I'd recommend this place to any boba lover.

reviews_data.review_text: I placed a large order for my wedding and the donuts were a hit. All my guests loved the oreo, matcha, and strawberry flavored mochi donuts. I highly recommend Moji Teahouse for yummy mochi donuts.
Super nice place and their mango juice tastes great, love their popping boba and snack variety
Made a trip over to the area and was not disappointed! Service was quick and easy. No wait which was great. Happy with our order, tasted great. Nice atmosphere for photos too.
I tried this first time especially for donuts but i m so disappointed because donuts are cold it taste not good to me n drinks are ok
Love the interior and tasty food.

I don't know how good this place is.  My daughter bought a few tasty little snacks and a tee. I only know that she threw the tee away and didn't drink it. Also, she has not asked to go back. We have been by there many times since. Never had she asked to go back, not even once.
never tried asian donuts before. Love it! coming back for sure
Delicious honeydew milk tea. Very nice and helpful staff.
Love the atmosphere, really nice employees and awesome drinks 🧋:)

Amazing atmosphere and team members who want to help create a great community of Tea enjoyers!!

Thank You and I will be back to try more soon!!
Came for the moji donuts and was not disappointed 😋 it was good! The tea was is good too but interior design was so cute with felt livey. Nice employees as well
Their mochi donut was delicious. Their Boba tea was ok. The atmosphere is beautiful

I live in Asia so it's hard to impress me when it comes to Boba tea. However I was very impressed by this place and the drinks were delicious and the prices are reasonable. My only suggestion to the owner is to add more tapiokas to the large drinks because I ran out of them before I was finished with my drink. Usually in Asia you have plenty of tapiokas left after the drink part is done. But overall I'm satisfied and I'll be back!
Just meh
Tea is okay. Not the best. Raspberry donut is great.

I was craving bubble tea and man I was so disappointed in the tapioca balls. Some were  chewy and some were still hard, it could literally be a choking hazard. Please make sure your tapioca balls are cooked all the way. The drink would have been so perfect but I literally had to keep spitting out every other ball because it wasn't chewable. Donuts we're great though.
Love it..such a cute place with delicious coffee and donuts!
Probably best place to get bubble tea in Charlotte. We tried many and this place beats on all categories: flavor, design, cleanliness, choices etc.

This place is AMAZING! If you’ve been to Japan then you know this is just like Mister Donuts. I’ve been craving for their donuts and OMG! Now I don’t have to fly to Japan to get their donuts. This is the PLACE! Amazing customer service! ♥️
Love the bubble tea here, I always get the taro. The mango pearls are delicious and appreciate the ability to customize sugar and ice levels.
Boba was hard and took over 25 minutes to get my one drink
Great service, friendly staff, and delicious Mochi Donuts!
Nice and quite place to enjoy your drink. I love it. Thanks for a great service.
Delicious 🫠🫠🫠
Gotta try their little donuts, and the boba and coffee are always on point!

Tasty mochi donuts and a refreshing variety of teas and juices, only slightly pricey. Too bad its popularity made for a 40-minute standing wait to order and 30-minute standing wait to enjoy a to-go order. A very popular spot for hanging out on a Sunday afternoon for area young people further narrows limited seating for customers. Donut varieties number only six per week, though flavors are  changed often.
amazing place! great employees, wonderful service too. definitely recommend

Everything I had was so yummy!
Was eyeing out this place for a while and decided to give it a try. Had a Condensed  Milk Latte and it delivered the right coffee flavor and sweetness, my boyfriend had a coconut milk tea boba and it the flavor was really refreshing.
The mochi donuts became my new favorite treat, we had their valentine’s special flavors and all were great, especially the strawberry cheesecake (i think that’s what it was) and the sakura one, all of them fresh, fluffy and not overly sweet.

Definitely recommend this place!

super popular now so be prepared to wait in a line but the venue is BEAUTIFUL and the staff is incredible. well worth the wait. however I am sad they took spam musubi off of the menu and hope that item returns. they also have specials and decorations for holidays!

Try one of their yakult/yogurt drinks! My favorite is the strawberry. It's such a creamy and refreshing drink! Perfect if you're not a fan of milk tea. The staff is always super helpful and welcoming.
hella good
Great service and even greater drinks! The Coconut Milk Smoothie is to die for! 💯💯
Very lovely teahouse, there boba tea is one of the best i ever had would recommande.
This place is fire. Good food, (especially them donuts) and chill environment. I will definitely try to visit more often.
Best Tea place i’ve been to in a long time! Highly highly recommend.
Excellent customer service, seriously, they need more support!
Honestly amazing best staff ever
I love their Moji Boba Latte, their tapioca pearls are the best I’ve had in Charlotte.
Very bad customer service, change your mind if you planning to support this shop.

reviews_data.review_text: The brown sugar coffee latte is my favorite. This was my first time trying mochi donuts…I will not be going back to cake donuts. I’m excited to go back and try the macaroons on my next visit, they looked delicious.

reviews_data.review_text: I got a coconut bubble tea and it was delicious, you can request your level of sugar so it’s not too sweet. First time trying mochi donuts and it was so yummy!! Will be back again!
Very friendly folks
Favorite tea place, always excited to come here.
Wide menu, very tasty, great service.

Beautiful tea bar where you can enjoy a cozy atmosphere, boba tea, mochi donuts, and much more. Things are priced fairly and I'm glad this place opened up so close to the outlets! They have a variety of boba pearls including mango and brown sugar which we love.
Friendly staff + very calm atmosphere

reviews_data.review_text:
I ordered Roasted Oolong Milk Tea with Boba. And 1/2 dozen of Mochi donuts( Strawberry Matcha, Frusty, Christmas something..etc). And Panda Coconut Waffle. I am so glad to visit here. It's far from my home. But it was definitely worth it.  And I can choose Oatmilk for Oolong Milk tea!! The taste is sooo amazing . I recommend Strawberry Matcha, Rudolph Mochi Donut. Also, the interior was so cute :) I will definitely visit again  :)

(The only thing that would've made it even better was if the Mochi Donut had been warm;))

Such a cute shop and the customer service was fantastic! The gentleman who helped us helped me pick out what I wanted without acting annoyed or frustrated I was needing help (pregnant and needed boba thats caffeine free and wasn't sure on my options). Super fast in preparation and everything was SO GOOD. Will absolutely be going back.
This place was adorable ! We enjoyed a Boba tea and a variety of mochi donuts that were fantastic! The customer service was great. We can’t wait to return .
Dulce de Leche, Fruity Pebbles, and Strawberry Dragoonfruit!!!!!! So good!!!!!
Good boba, some drinks are diff like thai tea but oolong & jasmine milk tea r good
Very delicious! The mochi donuts (especially the matcha) were amazing! Definitely want to go back for other goodies!
10/10 recommend! My favorite drink is the taro milk tea with boba. The musubi and donuts are yummy as well.
Amazing boba tea and delicious donuts too!
Got the taro smoothie and it was ok. Ice wasn’t blended too well and some boba was very soft and some was slightly hard. Consistency was off but nice decors and clean building.
I love the mochi donuts and the milk tea!
This is my favorite place for boba tea! The cheese foam is so delicious 😋
Very good boba tea and donuts
moji doughnuts are unique and taste so good! Milk tea with bona are also good!

I am a repeat customer, and usually enjoy the tea. The young ladies at the register  are usually super nice, and patient. But today, my visit was not too satisfying, which is disappointing. I really like their tea, but sadly I will not be returning.
My complaint is:
I  arrived and  placed my drink order first,  prior to a caucasian gentleman,.
The  barista purposely made his drink before mine. I  politely asked why did the man get his  drink before me, and  the response was his drink was easier to make. That just did not sit right with me.
Orders should be made on a first come first  serve basis, and not which customer's drink is easier to make.
Being an African American woman,  or a person of color,  it made me feel uncomfortable , This type of   action towards a customer can be viewed  as discrimination, This incident may not have been intentional, but ,African Americans, or people of color do not always get the same customer service as  a non person of color. This is something that the  employee(s) of Moji Teahouse need to be mindful of. I see a lot of persons of color supporting the business,.
The employees may need some sensitivity training, or teaching tolerance lessons.. Sadly, I won't be returning because I enjoy the tea. I will take my business elsewhere.  Queen City Tea prepares their drinks on a first come first serve basis.
Fresh food, delicious drinks, and full of variety. the place is very cozy

Super yummy doughnuts! Their milk teas are really delicious too~
The decor is clean and chic, and even their hot cups are soooo pretty
So glad this is now a family owned business! Still offering great bubble tea, and now they offer delicious mochi doughnuts and other snacks.
Nice but need to wait sometime quite long time
Yummy assorted mochi donuts...banana, raspberry, cotton candy, chocolate pretzel, horchata, and coconut. Brown Sugar Milk Tea with Boba and Thai Tea with bobas.
So delicious! They have a huge selection of flavors and toppings. It’s super fresh and they’re always quick with service!
Loved their mochi donuts!
Love these Mochi donuts, and the drinks are amazing.  We went twice in 2 days and neither day disappointed!  Love the weekly change of flavors.
Love this place. Everything is delicious. Sometimes there is a wait but it’s so worth it. I recommend the Pandan waffle is so delicious!!

Very cute Boba tea shop! Every Monday will be busy due to daily weeks of different donuts flavors. They hand out buzzers for orders to be ready. They have golden boba/tapioca which other places does not. Which is similar to black/regular tapioca. Location used to be Ding Tea.

I found this place through Instagram and decided to try it out. It's a cute tiny place but it sure is quite popular. They have some adorable merchandise that looked for sale. They also had a small bench swing for photo opportunities. The selection was pretty big, and allowing for sugar and/or ice amount changes. I mainly came here for the mochi donuts. I had a pandan coconut Waffle, mochi donut and milk tea. It was reminiscent of shops you would find on the west coast. Even with 25% sugar, I found the tea to be a little too sweet. The Waffle was spongy and slightly sweet and just right for me. The donut had the chewy texture which I expected but just like the tea, it was a tad too sweet for my liking. Very cute aesthetic and good pricing.

Came the first time when they rebranded asked for 4 different things on the menu literally out of everything decided to just leave. Came back on a Tuesday,waited about 40 minutes for 2mochi donuts,not worth the money.stale donuts.

Found this place on instagram. We went on a Sunday and the line was very long. We waited about 25 mins to order. I ordered a mochi donut which was kind of expensive ($3.50) a large tarp smoothie and 2 spam musbi which were delicious. The place is beautiful inside as well
fire donuts
The team here is awesome. Order is always on point. Come see them.
the moji boba latte is the milk base and brown sugar boba, it’s so good! i finished and honestly wish i got a bigger one!

Been a regular since before they rebranded. I went 3 times this past week, and my last visit was the day after the Instagram post. Of course, due to the post the line was long and so was the wait time. But the staff was as friendly as usual and they were working diligently to get the orders out as best they could under the circumstances. Their boba tea is delicious and so are their Mochi Donuts. If you’re visiting for the first time since the Instagram post, be patient because, of course wait times will be longer than usual. But their friendliness and positive attitude certainly compensates the wait. Enjoy the Moji Teahouse experience as well as the cute aesthetic look, everyone! 🙂

I saw good reviews on this location. I arrived around 11:48am ish and things went smoothly. Each donut is $3.50 each (plus tax). That's a bit expensive for me. I believe a dozen costs $30. I bought a milk tea and 1 donut. The donut was good, but I don't think it was worth $3.50. After I order, more people started to arrive. The line ended outside (the entrance of the store.) It was getting very crowded and I decided to leave. If you plan on coming here, get there early.
As for the Milk tea, it's average. I would rather go to gong Cha.

Waited 30 minutes to order 3 mochi doughnuts. Then another 40 minutes just to get them despite plenty of doughnuts waiting on the shelves as the staff were busy making bubble tea orders. You'd think orders with ready made items could've been fulfilled before others just to get customers out the door. Staff were slow and unorganised with no sense of urgency despite the queue out the door.

Doughnuts were decent at least.

Came here on a Friday afternoon. We expected not to be crowded but there was a line. We waited 30 mins to get to the front of the line. People were waiting to get their boba drinks for seemingly a long time. We decided to skip beverages since it seemed like the wait for boba was taking too long. We just ordered 3 mochi donuts so we didn’t have to wait another 30+ mins. Don’t come here if you have somewhere to be! Hoping that when Mochinuts opens soon, the ordering process will be smoother and faster. Drove down here from Concord. Will not return.

My husband and I tried Ding Tea, but just recently came back for the first time since they rebranded and changed up their menu a bit.

We shared:
- Pandan Coconut Waffle
- Lychee Strawberry and Passion Fruit Mochi Donuts
